HEADWORD: Sundown
<hw>Sun"down`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
setting of the sun; sunset.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧When <xex>sundown</xex> skirts
the moor.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of broad-brimmed sun hat worn by
women.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sundowner</ent>⟦br⟧
